  "original_title": "\u0b9c\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baa\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0ba4\u0bae\u0bb0\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b89\u0b9f\u0ba9\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0b95 \u0baa\u0ba4\u0bb5\u0bbf \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0b95 \u0bb5\u0bc7\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd :  \u0b95\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd \u0ba4\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0bb5\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b95\u0bc2\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0b90\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf\u0baf \u0bae\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0b9a\u0b95\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf \u0baa\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc7\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbe\u0ba4\u0bc1 - \u0b9a\u0b9c\u0bbf\u0ba4\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "President and PM should resign immediately: United People's Shakti will not participate in party leaders' meeting - Sajith",
      "author": "Digital Desk 5",
      "body_lines": [
        "Leader of the Opposition Sajith Premadasa said that as the people of the country are demanding that Gotabaya Rajapaksa and the current Prime Minister who does not have a people's mandate should step down and go home, we would like to inform you that United People's Power will not participate in the discussions called by Ranil Wickremesinghe, who is currently serving as Prime Minister illegally.",
        "In the media statement sent to United People's Shakti Media, it is further mentioned that,",
        "It should be mentioned that the present Prime Minister is the one who betrayed the struggle and he is also the defendant in this crisis when the Rajapaksas who were hiding in the middle of the people's opposition were brought back to the political arena and secured.",
        "We are not going to engage in empty discussions like closing the stables after the horse has run, when the end of an arbitrary, repressive, and undemocratic government is now in sight.",
        "At a time when all the people of this country are united in the single goal of building our lovely motherland, the goal of victory is within reach, yet another futile discussion called by a bogus prime minister is to ensure the safety of the Rajapakses yet another round. The entire government should resign from such unstable solutions.",
        "We do not want to discuss the future of the country with the guardians and gatekeepers of the government led by Gotabaya Rajapaksa, and we also say that we will contribute to building this country in collaboration with all parties who have come forward with the people's struggle."
      ],
